◆ VECTOR_STRUCT

#define VECTOR_STRUCT (   type,
  dtype 
)     typedef struct {type *array; size_t allocated_length; size_t active_length; mem_type dat_type; } dtype

This macro will produce a struct that is specifically designed to track all attributes necessary for the maintenance of a dynamically, or statically allocated array. The macro has an attribute to a pointer for the array, allocated_length, active_length, and mem_type.

/param type The data type that will be assigned to the array pointer /param dtype The name to be given to the typedef for the struct

// code to create a struct of type IntVector

◆ delete_bool_vector_duplicates()

void delete_bool_vector_duplicates ( Bool *  vec)

This function will delete all duplicate values in a Bool struct, with exception of the first instance of the variable.

/param vec A struct container of type Bool

init_bool_vector(vec, 6);
push_bool_vector(vec, true);

◆ push_string_vector()

int push_string_vector ( String *  vec,
char *  value,
size_t  index 
)

This function will push a single string to an existing string vector container

/param vec A vector struct of type String /param value A string /param index The index where the string is to be pushed

#include "vector.h"
#include "print.h"
String vec;
init_string_vector(vec);
push_string_vector(&vec, "Hello", 0);
push_string_vector(&vec, "Goodbye", 1);
push_string_vector(&vec, "Again", 0);
PRINT(vec);
// >> [ Again, Hello, Goodbye ]
free_string_vector(&vec);

This function will sort a vector data structure of type UInt in forward or reverse order

/param vec A vector data structure of type UInt /param low The lowest indice for partitioning, recommended to be 0 /param high The highest indice for sorting, recommended to be the last index in the data structure /param order FORWARD for a forward sort, REVERSE for a reverse sort

3266 // To find integral part of square
3267 // root of number
3268 while (start <= end) {
3269 // Find mid
3270 mid = (start + end) / 2;
3271 // If number is perfect square
3272 // then break
3273 if (mid * mid == number) {
3274 ans = mid;
3275 break;
3276 }
3277 // Increment start if integral
3278 // part lies on right side
3279 // of the mid
3280 if (mid * mid < number) {
3281 //first start value should be added to answer
3282 ans=start;
3283 //then start should be changed
3284 start = mid + 1.f;
3285 }
3286 // Decrement end if integral part
3287 // lies on the left side of the mid
3288 else {
3289 end = mid - 1.f;
3290 }
3291 }
3292 // To find the fractional part
3293 // of square root upto 5 decimal
3294 float increment = 0.1f;
3295 for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
3296 while (ans * ans <= number) {
3297 ans += increment;
3298 }
3299 // Loop terminates,
3300 // when ans * ans > number
3301 ans = ans - increment;
3302 increment = increment / 10;
3303 }
3304 return ans;
3305}
